## D8. What §2.5 does NOT do — end-to-end SHUD simulation is scope-deferred
# The §2.3 synthetic package is a **direct-grid CONTRACT fixture**: it carries
# only the direct-grid-specific inputs (`.sp.att` with multi-station FORC,
# `.tsd.forc` multi-station forcing header, per-station CSVs, binding-manifest).
# It is NOT a full SHUD project — it is missing the other input files SHUD
# needs to actually simulate: `.sp.mesh` (mesh triangulation), `.sp.riv`
# (river network), `.sp.rivseg` (river segments), `.para.lc/geol/soil` (LC/geology/
# soil parameter sets), `.tsd.lai/mf/rl` (time-series LAI/melt-factor/roughness),
# and `.cfg.para/calib/ic` (config + calibration + initial conditions).
#
# Reference (verified against production basins on node-27, 2026-07-07 UTC).
# Authoritative production model release for qhh is the object-store
# release-frozen package:
#   /home/ghdc/nwm/object-store/models/basins_qhh_shud/
#   vbasins-qhh-baf3aaf479de-c58dfb94-calibfix20260630/package/
# with matching manifest.json + 18 SHUD input files (~2 MiB). node-27's
# basin-owner workspace at `/home/ghdc/nwm/Basins/qhh/input/qhh/` and
# node-22's replica at `/volume/nwm/Basins/qhh/input/qhh/` are identical-
# content mirrors of the same modeling inputs (verified: 4,773 elements,
# 386 stations, 347 unique FORC values, X<lon>Y<lat>.csv per-station
# grid-derived filename pattern, currently legacy IDW-consumed).
#
